# Architecture Output Rule

When asked to design or modify architecture, provide senior-level reasoning.

Always include:
- recommended approach
- why this approach is appropriate
- alternatives considered
- trade-offs
- risks
- testing strategy
- migration or rollout strategy if applicable

When asked to implement code, be concise but explain important architectural decisions.

Do not hide complexity.

Do not pretend distributed systems are simple.

If a microservice is proposed, include:
- service boundary
- owned data
- API/event contracts
- consistency model
- failure handling
- deployment implications
- observability requirements

